<HEADLINE>
<P>
CULTURAL CLASH IN SAUDI ARABIA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Saudi Arabia's recent political actions repressing women make it clear that the 
United States is not in the Persian Gulf to protect freedom, democracy or human 
rights. We should not use our resources or the men and women of our armed 
forces to defend the interests of a country that subjugates a segment of its 
people. We will never set the moral standard for the world as long as we 
continue to compromise our principles. 
</P>
<P>
ROCHELLE M. LINDSEY 
</P>
<P>
JODY COHAN 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
