<HEADLINE>
<P>
GRACE C. MACINNES; RETIRED TEACHER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Grace C. MacInnes, a longtime resident of Van Nuys who taught elementary school 
classes in the San Fernando Valley for 22 years, has died in a Simi Valley 
nursing home. 
</P>
<P>
She was 67. 
</P>
<P>
Mrs. MacInnes died Saturday of cancer, said her daughter-in-law, Carol 
MacInnes. 
</P>
<P>
Born June 22, 1923, in Newark, N.Y., she came to California in 1942 and later 
earned a bachelor's degree and teaching credential from San Fernando Valley 
State College -- now Cal State Northridge. She began teaching in 1966, working 
at several San Fernando Valley elementary schools, including Langdon Avenue 
School in Sepulveda. Mrs. MacInnes retired two years ago from Beachy Avenue 
School in Arleta, where she taught third grade. 
</P>
<P>
She is survived by her son, Scott MacInnes of Simi Valley; a daughter, Bonnie 
MacInnes of San Francisco; mother, Anna Burzynski of Hollywood; brothers Jerry 
Burzynski of Hollywood and Jim Burzynski of Arkansas; sisters Dorothy Martino 
and Joyce Curtis of Hollywood; and four grandchildren. Her husband, John 
MacInnes, died in 1980. 
</P>
<P>
A funeral, with burial to follow, is planned at 1:30 p.m. Friday at the Old 
North Church at Forest Lawn Memorial-Park, 6300 Forest Lawn Drive, in the 
Hollywood Hills. Donations can be made to a memorial fund in Mrs. MacInnes' 
name at St. Mark's Presbyterian Church in Van Nuys. 
</P>
</TEXT>
