<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Yields on 5-Year Notes Fall: The Treasury reported that the average yield was 
7.95%, down from 8.57% at the last auction on Aug. 29. 
</P>
<P>
It was the lowest rate since five-year notes averaged 7.77% on Nov. 29, 1989. 
The notes will carry a coupon interest rate of 7.875%, with each $10,000 in 
face value selling for $9,962.60. A total of $9.04 billion in notes were sold 
out of bids totaling $22.99 billion. 
</P>
</TEXT>
