WESTSIDE DIGEST: BEVERLY HILLS; 
</P>
<P>
STUDENTS TO RECYCLE SUPPLIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Associated Student Body at Beverly Hills High School has put aside $1,000 
to purchase 200 boxes to be used in a recycling effort at the school. The 
boxes, which will be used to collect notebook and Xerox paper as well as other 
supplies, will be placed in rooms throughout the high school and in school 
district offices. 
</P>
<P>
A salvage company will pay the student body office a percentage of the selling 
price for the recycled goods. 
</P>
