<HEADLINE>
<P>
WESTSIDE DIGEST: VENICE; 
</P>
<P>
COASTAL LAND-USE PLAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Los Angeles city planners will present an overview of a proposed coastal land 
use plan for the Venice area at an informational meeting next Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
The long overdue document, required by the California Coastal Act, includes 
goals for future development of the area as well as provisions for ensuring 
public access to the shoreline. The plan also details how the city intends to 
provide recreational and visitor facilities in the coastal area. 
</P>
<P>
The meeting will be held from 5 p.m. to 8 p.m. Tuesday at the Venice High 
School auditorium, 13000 Venice Blvd. 
</P>
<P>
A public hearing on the plan will be conducted by the Los Angeles Planning 
Commission at 10 a.m. Jan. 3 in Room 340 of City Hall. 
</P>
</TEXT>
