<HEADLINE>
<P>
BEST BET 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By R.D. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Astronomer Andrew Fraknoi's "Other Worlds: A Grand Tour of the Solar System" 
certainly interests us. We have a strong suspicion that we're from outer space, 
since not a day goes by that someone doesn't ask: "What planet are you from?" 
The program will include images sent back by U.S., Soviet and European 
spacecraft, and the latest information from telescopes on Earth and in space. 
</P>
<P>
And Fraknoi, who's executive director of the Astronomical Society of the 
Pacific, promises his discussion of the subject won't even contain a syllable 
of NASAspeak. Just plain, everyday language about the rings of Saturn, 
Jupiter's stormy moon Io, asteroids, the search for Planet X and more. It will 
be held Saturday from 9 a.m. to 5 p.m. in Room 2160E of the Dickson Art Center 
at UCLA. Fees vary. For information call (213) 825-7093. Klaatu, barada, nikto. 
R.D. 
</P>
</TEXT>
