<P>
VENTURA COUNTY NEWS ROUNDUP: SANTA PAULA; 
</P>
<P>
MAN ARRESTED AFTER CRASH KILLS BROTHER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CAROL WATSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 27-year-old Santa Paula man was arrested on suspicion of felony drunk driving 
Tuesday after the car he was driving crashed and his older brother was killed, 
authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
Guadalupe Garcia Cantero, 29, of Santa Paula died instantly of head injuries in 
the crash, according to the Ventura County coroner's office. 
</P>
<P>
He was riding in the back seat of the 1984 Plymouth Colt driven by his brother, 
Robert Garcia Cantero, when the accident occurred about 1 a.m., authorities 
said. 
</P>
<P>
Cantero was driving south on California 150 south of Bridge Road at about 85 
m.p.h, California Highway Patrol Officer Jim Utter said. The car missed a curve 
and went off the right side of the road, hitting a parked pickup truck and a 
van, Utter said. The car then skidded and struck a power pole, he said. 
</P>
<P>
Cantero was arrested and taken to Santa Paula Memorial Hospital, where he was 
listed in fair condition, a hospital spokeswoman said. Another passenger, 
William Lugo, 29, suffered minor injuries and was treated at the hospital and 
released, the spokeswoman said. CAROL WATSON 
</P>
</TEXT>
