for 24 hours. ; Photo, Nineteen-year-old Kristie Schmidt of Northridge 
determines what time it is by using her hands to gauge the position of the sun. 
It's one of the skills the students learn in the class. ; Photo, One of the 
delicacies eaten by the students is thistle root, which is peeled like a 
carrot. They also dined on lizard stew. At the end of the 48-hour expedition in 
the wilderness, Jose Campos, 20, packs up his gear and gets ready for the 
return trip to civilization. ; Photo, Luke Giese, 25, of Hollywood and Michelle 
Nevins, 20, of North Hollywood wake up in their makeshift home outdoors. ; 
Photo, Storme Warren is escorted silently by a group of teaching assistants in 
the class to a remote corner of the camp area for his 24 hours of exile. ; 
