<HEADLINE>
<P>
BOOKS &amp; AUTHORS: A NEWSLETTER THAT'S JUST FOR KIDS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DENNIS McLELLAN, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Nancy Ann Van Wie of Laguna Hills, who writes and publishes the "Travels With 
Max" series of travel and activity books for young children, is now publishing 
a children's newsletter to encourage children "to experience and explore the 
rewards of reading." 
</P>
<P>
"Travels With Max -- A Newsletter Just for Kids," introduces children to 
faraway places, different cultures, current events and human interest stories. 
</P>
<P>
Van Wie says the newsletter, which is aimed at children aged 7 through 11, also 
allows them to participate in the actual content of the newsletter. 
</P>
<P>
"Kids are encouraged to send in ideas on stories, their favorite books, 
riddles, recipes and information on themselves if they want a pen pal," says 
Van Wie, who has a master's degree in education and is the author and creator 
of the United Airlines Fun Book, "J.P. Jetsetter, King of the Friendly Skies." 
</P>
<P>
The newsletter will be published seven times a year. For further information, 
call Max's Hotline at (800) 4-MAX-OO8. 
</P>
</TEXT>
