<P>
RAMS; 
</P>
<P>
ROBINSON SAYS ELLARD CAN PLAY AGAINST BROWNS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TIM KAWAKAMI 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Ram receiver Henry Ellard, who was held out of last week's game with a sore 
right hamstring, is healthy enough to play this Sunday's game at Cleveland, 
Coach John Robinson said. 
</P>
<P>
But Robinson also said that Aaron Cox, who started in Ellard's place Sunday but 
had to leave with a sore hamstring, probably won't be ready for the game 
against the Browns. 
</P>
<P>
Finishing up the sore hamstring news, Robinson said he wasn't sure whether 
starting tight end Damone Johnson could play. Cox and Johnson are listed as 
questionable and Ellard is listed as probable. 
</P>
<P>
The Rams signed linebacker Bruce Klostermann to take the special teams duties 
of linebacker Greg Clark, who was placed on injured reserve after breaking a 
bone in his right leg last Sunday. TIM KAWAKAMI 
