<TEXT>
<P>
Subaru Cuts Work Force: Subaru of America Inc. will trim its 1,080-person work 
force by as much as 10% to cut costs and restore profitability, a company 
spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
Some employees have been notified that they will be let go, effective Dec. 28, 
and other reductions will be made over the next few months, spokesman Richard 
Marshall said. He said the layoffs would affect the company's Cherry Hill, 
N.J., headquarters, a Pennsauken, N.J., facility, regional offices in West Palm 
Beach, Fla., and Savage, Md. Subaru of America, owned by Fuji Heavy Industries 
Ltd. of Japan, suffered losses of $42.4 million last year. 
