<P>
USX Chief in No Hurry to Meet Icahn Group: Chairman Charles A. Corry is in no 
hurry to meet with a committee formed by Carl C. Icahn to press the financier's 
case that the company should separate its steel and energy businesses. Two 
professors heading the "USX Shareholders Enhancement Committee" wrote a letter 
to Corry on Nov. 15 requesting that he meet with them to discuss the company's 
future. 
</P>
