<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: WEST COVINA; 
</P>
<P>
SHUTTLE CONTRACT OKD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The City Council on Monday unanimously approved a three-year contract with 
Community Transit Services Inc. to continue its shuttle service to the city. 
</P>
<P>
The service began in April, 1988, transporting riders from Eastland Center mall 
and Restaurant Row to Fashion Plaza and the Civic Center. 
</P>
<P>
Last year the route was adjusted to include the Queen of the Valley Hospital 
area. It increased ridership from 4,500 to 7,000 monthly. 
</P>
<P>
Total cost of the new contract is $1,169,562, which will come from Proposition 
A funds, the half-cent sales tax earmarked for local transportation. 
</P>
<P>
The new contract takes effect in July, but the old one expires in April. In 
order to continue uninterrupted shuttle service, the council voted to 
appropriate $100,000 to fund the service in the interim. 
</P>
</TEXT>
