<P>
SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: EL MONTE; 
</P>
<P>
SUBDIVISION APPEAL DENIED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Time finally ran out Tuesday for a proposed subdivision on Edwards Avenue south 
of Garvey Avenue. 
</P>
<P>
The City Council upheld the Planning Commission's May 21 ruling against the 
eight-home project, despite testimony from neighbors. The neighbors said the 
project would bring improvements to an area plagued by drug trafficking. 
</P>
<P>
Owner Fun S. Psang had appealed the Planning Commission ruling and proposed 
widening Edwards Avenue. 
</P>
<P>
In rejecting the proposal last May, the commission said Edwards, a short 
private road, was unsuitable for a project of that density. City Planning 
Director Harold Johanson said Tuesday that although Psang's changes improved 
the project, additional study of the proposal was needed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
