SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: DUARTE; 
</P>
<P>
GINNY JOYCE CHOSEN MAYOR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Ginny Joyce on Tuesday became the city's first female mayor. 
</P>
<P>
She was unanimously selected for the post by fellow City Council members during 
the council's annual reorganization. 
</P>
<P>
John Van Doren was chosen to be mayor pro tem. 
</P>
<P>
Joyce, 52, was elected to the council in November, 1988, and was chosen mayor 
pro tem in November, 1989. 
</P>
<P>
She said that her selection is symbolic of the advances women are making in 
politics and that she is excited to be the first female mayor in Duarte. 
</P>
<P>
Each year, council members select a mayor from among their ranks to serve a 
one-year term. 
</P>
