49ERS BASKETBALL TEAM WILL PLAY AT UNDEFEATED ARIZONA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Cal State Long Beach men's basketball team, which has yet to exhibit any of 
its preseason promise, will play No. 2-ranked Arizona at 3 p.m. Saturday in 
Tucson's McKale Center. 
</P>
<P>
The game will be broadcast by KORG (1190). 
</P>
<P>
After barely getting by Chicago State, 84-81, Monday night in their home 
opener, the 49ers are 1-1. They lost last Saturday night at North Texas, 94-82. 
</P>
<P>
Long Beach is shooting only 39% from the field and has made 50 turnovers. 
Sophomore guard Lucious Harris is leading the 49ers with an average of 28 
points a game. 
</P>
<P>
Arizona is 5-0 after beating Western Illinois, 90-51, Monday night. 
</P>
