<HEADLINE>
<P>
2 HORSES, 2 DIFFERENT ROUTES TO A REMATCH; 
</P>
<P>
HORSE RACE: TOOTER SCOOTER BASKED IN FLORIDA SUN WHILE DIE LAUGHING WORKED OUT 
UP NORTH. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
POMPANO BEACH, Fla. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Tooter Scooter and Die Laughing have taken different paths to their rematch 
Friday in the Breeders Crown. 
</P>
<P>
When the two colts last met, Tooter Scooter tailed Die Laughing from start to 
finish in a stakes pace at the Red Mile in Lexington, Ky. 
</P>
<P>
While Tooter Scooter has been basking in the warmth of South Florida since that 
loss in October, Die Laughing has been put through a rigorous prep program in 
the cooler North. The different schedules could weigh in Tooter Scooter's 
favor, Joe Holloway, the colt's trainer, said. 
</P>
<P>
"My horse has been down here lying on the beach and sending out post cards," 
Holloway said. "Die Laughing has been up North running in four or five tough 
races." 
</P>
<P>
Nonetheless, Die Laughing has been made the 9-5 morning-line favorite to win 
the $605,870 Colt and Gelding Pace, one of four Breeders Crown races Friday 
night at Pompano Harness Track. The card for 2-year-olds is the last of 12 
Breeders Crown events for 1990. 
</P>
<P>
Artsplace, who has won 10 of 14 starts this year, was made the second choice at 
5-2. Tooter Scooter is the track handicapper's 6-1 third pick. 
</P>
<P>
"I think the track handicapper is about right," Holloway said. 
</P>
<P>
Die Laughing, after all, has earned more than $1.1 million while winning eight 
of 11 starts this year. He won the Presidential at Maryland's Rosecroft in 
early November and was second by half a length to Artsplace in the Nov. 17 
Governors Cup at New Jersey's Garden State Park. 
</P>
<P>
By comparison, Tooter Scooter has earned just $388,000 while winning six of 16 
starts. But he has finished no worse than second in any of his last eight 
starts, including a victory in the Kentucky Pace Derby at Louisville Downs in 
September. 
</P>
</TEXT>
