<P>
TENNESSEE ERNIE STILL 'THRILLED' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NASHVILLE, Tenn. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
It's been a few weeks since Tennessee Ernie Ford was elected to the Country 
Music Hall of Fame, but he says he still hasn't come out of the clouds. 
</P>
<P>
"I've got the gear down, but I'm not quite on the ground," Ford said. 
</P>
<P>
"It was totally a surprise because I had some pretty stiff competition. 
Needless to say, I'm thrilled." 
</P>
<P>
Ford received the prestigious award during the Country Music Assn.'s Awards 
show telecast here Oct. 8. 
</P>
<P>
"It means that over the years, you have accomplished something in your career," 
Ford said. "It meant so much to me, and it gave me a very nice warm feeling, 
with the people, the way they reacted, the way they stood up that night." 
</P>
<P>
"The nicest thing that people say to me now wherever I go is 'I feel like I 
know you.' That's before they say anything about the show or about my singing. 
'I feel like I know you.' " 
</P>
</TEXT>
